dataIdInfo.idPurp: This shapefile represents the current stock boundary for common bottlenose dolphins around Hawaii Island in the main Hawaiian Islands.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This shapefile represents the current stock boundary for common bottlenose dolphins around Hawaii Island in the main Hawaiian Islands. This boundary is based on the 1,000 m isobath. Biological data have suggested that bottlenose dolphins within this boundary are demographically independent. More information on this boundary and other bottlenose dolphin stocks can be found in the latest stock assessment report.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: This shapefile was created from archived point data by Amanda Bradford <amanda.bradford@noaa.gov> at the NOAA Fisheries Pacific Islands Fisheries Science Center. The current projection is WGS_1984_UTM_Zone_4N.
